HEADWORD: noninheritable
<hw>noninheritable</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <def>not capable of transmission
by heredity. Opposite of <ant>inheritable</ant>.</def> [Narrower terms:
<stype>acquired, nurtural</stype>; <stype>congenital, inborn,
innate</stype>]⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> nonheritable, nonhereditary,
nontransmissible.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>noninstitutional</ent>⟦br⟧
